text: One of the few places for a good chill at karaoke pub. The owner is superbly friendly. The ambience is well decorated. They have private karaoke rooms and open space karaoke with good system. They have one pool table and per game is $2 only. You can change $1 coins there to play.  For foods, they have titbits only as they donâ€™t have kitchen. Overall surrounding is clean, chill and lively.

Soft Drinks are sold at $10 nett. They have a wide range of songs for karaoke and lots of alcohol. A friendly uncle runs the place and he was undisturbed by our horrible singing. There is also a pool table for people to enjoy!

I inquired about the status of my song dedication, but was told to wait and not bother the staff. While I understand the need to manage workload, I had hoped for a more helpful and communicative response. Hopefully, the team will work on improving their customer service in the future

No frills karaoke bar managed by an elderly couple. Super friendly and very pleasant place to hangout.

Pool table and affordable drinks with common area karaoke. Patrons there seem to be regulars and making it even friendlier.
Affordable no-frills karaoke that comes with a free drink per pax! Song selections were well updated too.
